Package: ucminfcpp
Title: Unconstrained Nonlinear Optimization via Modern C++ and Rcpp
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hans Bruun", "Nielsen", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original Fortran algorithm"),
    person("Stig Bousgaard", "Mortensen", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original R/Fortran/C implementation"),
    person("ucminfcpp", "Maintainer", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maintainer@example.com")
  )
Description: A modern C++17 reimplementation of the UCMINF unconstrained
    nonlinear optimization algorithm. The core algorithm uses RAII,
    STL containers (std::vector), and std::function for a clean,
    pointer-free API. An Rcpp interface exposes the optimizer to R,
    while pybind11 and CxxWrap bindings enable use from Python and Julia.
    The algorithm is of quasi-Newton type with BFGS updating of the inverse
    Hessian and a soft line search with trust-region radius monitoring.
